author: @Moorooten
text: I really like your stuf but this time I just want to scream at you "of course your input_generator does not yield anything if no key is being pressed", no frames are getting added becauese the generator is waiting for input. Keep spamming a key and you will get a recording but I guess you realized that by now.  You are trying to do parallell work here so your solution could be to use threads (maybe a bit ugly) otherwise i would look into if curtsies, curses (https://docs.python.org/3/howto/curses.html) or possibly termios has a non-blocking input call

author: @AminA-2051
text: I did something similar to you, but I believe the problem that arises when using Input from curtsies is that it requires a for loop that keeps querying for text input in real time. Since you also need the recording to be saved to frames in real time, you are going to have a bit of trouble using both pyaudio and curtsies. I don't know if that makes total sense, but that's my take on it. I slightly altered your code to just use a keypress notification (keyboard.is_pressed) that, on keypress, lets you run whatever code you want when you want to start and stop the recording. I'm attaching my code below if you wanted to take a look at it:  https://gist.github.com/Aminsteir/a69b06ea297400ef1341247e9c79b490

author: @Indemere
text: Hi Sentdex, so the key detection â€œfor e in...â€ doesnâ€™t iterate until you press a key. It is stuck on a yield that awaits a key press. Basically, it wont enter the for loop until some key is pressed and then loops once before waiting again for the next key. Thatâ€™s why itâ€™s not writing chunks. You might have to use a separate thread that constantly reads the keyboard and updates some variable that you read every time in your while loop that writes the audio to disk.  While true: if done_record_pressed: break Else: Data=... Frames.append(data)  I recommend Pynput for easy keyboard monitoring using threads. They have great documentation and examples. Feel free to ask me any question if you run into problems.
